From: Nicolas Grunbaum <ngrunbaum@mozilla.com>
Date: Tue, 16 Jun 2026 09:59:53 -0700
Subject: (tmp-cherry-pick) Revert "srtp: add UseCryptex API to SrtpSession and
 SrtpTransport" (264b57cf94)

This reverts commit b9386f3f09ba0f38320f6a9e65dfe2992f433cb5.

Reason for revert: Downstream libSRTP is not updated yet

Original change's description:
> srtp: add UseCryptex API to SrtpSession and SrtpTransport
>
> Adds the UseCryptex(enable, require, sending_session) API on SrtpSession
> and UseCryptex(enable, require) on SrtpTransport. Wires libsrtp's
> srtp_set_stream_use_cryptex through DoSetKey, and adds a require-cryptex
> post-decrypt check via ParseRtpExtensionProfile (new helper in
> modules/rtp_rtcp/source/rtp_util) for the cases libsrtp does not yet
> enforce; see https://github.com/cisco/libsrtp/pull/805.
>
> No callers yet; the cryptex SDP negotiation wires this up in a follow-up.
>
> Bug: webrtc:455813732
